My VIM config is optimized for using Vim in Iterm 2 on OS X.
But it shouldn't be too difficult to reconfigure it to use with Gvim/Macvim.

In order to use this config do next:
Install font 'Monaco for Powerline'

$ git clone https://github.com/constan4in/dotvim.git ~/.vim
$ ln -s ~/.vim/gvimrc ~/.vimrc

Install Vundle

$ git clone https://github.com/VundleVim/Vundle.vim.git ~/.vim/bundle/Vundle.vim

Install plugins

$ vim ~/.vimrc

Run the following command in vim
:BundleInstall

